        void onBaseFileReceived(File baseFile)
        Called when the basefile has been received. The client will not use the base file after this method returns, and will attempt to delete it when it leaves the session.
        Parameters:
        baseFile - The base file

        Called when the client has received an event.
        Parameters:
        orderId - The order id of the received event
        submissionRegistrationId - The submission registration id for the event
        eventType - The event type string passed in by the event broadcaster
        data - The event
        elapsed - Approximately how much time has passed since this event was originally received on the server in milliseconds

      • onSessionEnd

        void onSessionEnd(long id)
        Called when the current session has been ended by it's owner. Participants can still retrieve events and leave the session, but they can't broadcast or rejoin the session once they left
        Parameters:
        id - Id of session that ended
